(1) In these Regulations—

"adult worker" means a worker who has attained the age of 18;

"night time", in relation to a worker, means a period the duration of which is not less than seven hours, and which includes the period between midnight and 5 a.m., which is determined by a relevant agreement, or, in default, the period between 11 p.m. and 6 a.m.;

"night worker" means a worker who, as a normal course, works at least three hours of his daily working time during night time;

"rest period", in relation to a worker, means any period which is not working time;

"worker" has the same meaning as in section 230(3) of the Employment Rights Act 1996 and includes agency workers;

"working time", in relation to a worker, means—
(a) any period during which he is working, at his employer's disposal and carrying out his activity or duties,
(b) any period during which he is receiving relevant training,
(c) any additional period which is to be treated as working time for the purpose of these Regulations under a relevant agreement.

(1) The following provisions shall not apply in relation to a worker if, by reason of the specific characteristics of his activity, he is an activity worker—
(a) regulation 10(1) (daily rest);
(b) regulation 11(1) and (2) (weekly rest);
(c) regulation 12(1) (rest breaks).

(2) "Activity worker" means a worker who works where the worker's activities involve the need for continuity of service or production, or where there is a foreseeable surge of activity.
